  "objective": "C3A-R2 adds a durable, executable, public-safe full-project multilingual correctness acceptance gate for the local/mock Checkpoint 3A controlled demo. The gate anchors supported-language evidence to backend/app/stage6.py language catalog status fields, requires every locally supported language to have current corpus evidence, refuses planned/unsupported Priority 2 fake success, validates source English, target script/direction, deterministic English reference, citation/source-span continuity, contextRefs, claimSupports, UI/stored/export/report parity, stale-evidence invalidation, and negative false-pass cases across a synthetic multi-document project corpus. Non-goals: arbitrary-project translation quality, raw uploaded knowledge-document translation API proof, provider quality, provider setup, real provider calls, paid spend, hosted deployment, public URL, public demo, public distribution, cloned identity runtime, real media, private strategy, private media, provider payload/output exposure, or production-readiness claims.",
